Cell[TextData[{
 "Keep in mind that this equation is solved for a fixed position of the \
nuclei in the Born-Oppenheimer approximation. Thus, we can solve this \
equation for different H\[Dash]A\[Dash]H bond angle and see how the relative \
energies and wavefunctions of the molecular orbitals change as a function of \
the bond angle. First, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s examine the case where the bond \
angle is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["180", "\[Degree]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6822ef18-c4c9-4335-a70d-97d6cca6a960"],
 ", as in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["BeH", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ccf56347-ac11-4778-8462-dbc5158a2505"],
 ". The obtained molecular orbitals are shown in Figure 11.2. There are two \
bonding \[Sigma] orbitals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "g"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b4d10f17-ccbf-493b-9fc1-4c0846170e4d"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "u"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "38c9f73d-a346-46cb-8d3e-f3289d8bf00a"],
 "), two degenerate nonbonding orbitals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"1", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Pi]", "u"]}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "71c6fa01-93b4-44e0-a02b-0b51a3663850"],
 ", and two antibonding \[Sigma] orbitals ( ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"3", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "g"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1dc514a8-d737-4686-9944-96d6b2bebac2"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "u"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f99004cf-f65e-4c80-a006-cf8e857897f0"],
 "). In this case, the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "g"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9ead0584-d966-48d9-81b7-99fe11f3b3be"],
 " and and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"3", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "g"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d90fcccb-c02f-4bfa-af98-78fcab4f41d0"],
 " orbitals originate primarily from mixing of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["s",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "H"]}]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
    3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.8132225103046436`*^9, 
