  "],ExpressionUUID->"1291de31-d55c-495a-a2f0-855d7054ecf0"],

Cell["\<\
Keep in mind that H\[UDoubleDot]ckel theory is highly approximate; it doesn\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t account for many of the interactions between electrons \
and thus only gives a rough picture of bonding. For a more accurate \
prediction of the structure of conjugated hydrocarbons, it is best to use \
more advanced electronic structure methods.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145153392899942`*^9, 3.814515406406187*^9}, {
  3.8145155178288293`*^9, 
  3.814515601560161*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"983757ef-f020-4eb4-87ac-\
2436b5586d9a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Beyond Ethene - Delocalization Energy", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145198976720266`*^9, 
  3.8145199327547393`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6a9860be-c56f-4768-baeb-\
3eb3fec791ad"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We can also apply the H\[UDoubleDot]ckel approximation to explain the \
stability of larger aromatic systems. Take the case of buta-1,3-diene (see \
Figure 11.5 for structure). Now there are four carbons, and we write the \
wavefunction of the \[Pi] molecular orbitals as a linear combination of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"2", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["p",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["z",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8142715408501225`*^9, 3.8142716264528427`*^9}, {
   3.8142716634962983`*^9, 3.81427166385531*^9}, {3.8142717090653296`*^9, 
   3.814271758882024*^9}, {3.8144305791172466`*^9, 3.8144305954419746`*^9}, {
   3.8144307461264753`*^9, 3.814430819988105*^9}, {3.8144315687851577`*^9, 
   3.814431572922325*^9}, {3.814514291539785*^9, 3.8145143370538917`*^9}, {
   3.8145144764075503`*^9, 3.814514479317971*^9}, {3.8145147262851176`*^9, 
   3.8145147287172513`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "361ebd8d-a586-4c24-8e50-318b4acdf347"],
 " orbitals on each atom. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814519985524846*^9, 3.8145201946179185`*^9}, {
  3.938870920712311*^9, 
  3.93887092081472*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5ebd7686-8105-419a-b763-\
774128db9b83"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "\[Pi]"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["p",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["zA",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["p",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["zB",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "3"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["p",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["zC",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "4"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["p",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["zD",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8142715408501225`*^9, 3.8142716264528427`*^9}, {
  3.8142716634962983`*^9, 3.81427166385531*^9}, {3.8142717090653296`*^9, 
  3.814271758882024*^9}, {3.8144305791172466`*^9, 3.8144305954419746`*^9}, {
  3.8144307461264753`*^9, 3.814430819988105*^9}, {3.8144315687851577`*^9, 
  3.814431572922325*^9}, {3.8145202156376853`*^9, 
  3.8145202299527807`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"86d2da88-91fb-4f72-b205-\
2d87f97a113e"],

Cell["The Hamiltonian and overlap matrices are now 4 \[Times] 4 matrices,", \
